node.text:
Sun Opposite Neptune ⊹
This alignment has us flowing through with our head in the clouds. You may have felt a bit of an anxious shift over the past few days, where your thoughts are foggy and scattered. Take your time and slow down to process through things. Channelling these anxieties and emotions into a creative outlet can help you to feel grounded and clarity. 
 
Strong Neptune energy heightens messages from spirit and messages in dreams. Try and journal down your dreams as soon as you wake up and then come back to these over the next few weeks to decipher. 

Majestic art is by @lilly_prinz

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Amy 𓇸 𖤓 • Empowering Astrology on September 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Mars Enters Libra bring balance back into your life and prioritise your pleasure'.

node.text:
Mars has now moved into the sign of Libra. 
Mars represents how we assert ourselves and take action. When this planet moves into the peace loving and harmonious sign of Libra we can feel a little unmotivated. 

Mars in Libra helps bring balance back into our lives after a very goal oriented driven Virgo Mars cycle. This time is about taking a step back from the grind and let yourself have fun. Dive into your self care rituals, catch up with your friends, take yourself out on a date and do all the things that bring you joy and pleasure. 

Today’s journal prompt:
How can I bring more balance and self care into my days?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Amy 𓇸 𖤓 • Empowering Astrology on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'No amount of spiritual tools or products will advance your ascension if you aren't doing the inner work. Those items are purely material props that are there for your enjoyment. All that you need to be a spiritual being is already within you. Jisters Uellage'.

node.text:
Let’s talk about consumerism within the spiritual community. 

I’ve seen this concept of “spiritual shopping” quite a few times now, where people show the items that you “need” to advance your ascension. And I am just here to tell you that you don’t actually need anything. 

You don’t need the crystals or the incense or a tarot deck or spiritual books or just anything at all. Spirituality is a state of being, a deep knowing, you don’t need tools to get to this consciousness, you have the wisdom within you already, it’s all around.

So much of our world today is consumerist based and as spirituality becomes more popular, it becomes more commercialised. 

While purchasing or accumulating spiritual tools isn’t a bad thing at all if they bring you joy (we live in a material world, so enjoying material items come with this human existence) the point here is to be mindful about what you invest your money in and who you are investing your money in, and that you don’t actually need anything outside of yourself to be spiritual, thinking that you do is apart of the consumerism that is happening within the spiritual community right now.

If there is something that really calls you, that you are wanting to purchase that you believe is going to enrich your life, try and seek it out second hand or support a local, ethical business instead.

Let me know your thoughts? Have you gotten caught up in the “spiritual shopping” saga? Do you feel those spiritual tools enriched your life or have they just become clutter in your home?

node.text:
First Quarter Moon in Sagittarius ✻
The first quarter is the moon phase where we should begin to take action on the intentions we set on the new moon last week. 

Start putting things in place. It can be hard at times to take action, sometimes we doubt our own insights and intuitive pulls. Let this be the little nudge that you needed to take those leaps. Remember that you only have one life in this human body and it’s way too short to feel stuck where you are. Put yourself out there. 

When the Moon is in the expansive sign of Sagittarius we are guided towards growth. This is the time to become more aligned with your true self and authentic desires. Nothing is out of your reach.

Stepping into your power and putting yourself first will only ever push away those who were just there purely to take what they wanted from you anyway isters Uillage'.

node.text:
Today the Moon sits in the powerful sign of Scorpio and is making a square aspect to our expansive planet Jupiter. This energy is guiding us to really tap into our intuition on what has come up to the surface recently. These insights that are coming through are showing you the things you need to speak up about or set clear boundaries on. 

Always listen within and honour your feelings. 

Today is also a good time to delve deep into your shadow work. If you’re not sure what shadow work is or how to get started I have a guide/workbook for you to download and complete, which is under the ebooks section on my website ❍

Scorpio Venus is deep and passionate, the themes hat may come up for you during this time are here to guide you towards complete transformation and connection within your relationship. node.text:
Today Venus moves into the powerful and passionate sign of Scorpio. The theme for this season is self love, make the effort to love yourself a little extra this week. Take yourself on a date, wear your favourite outfits, eat your favourite food, give yourself a massage, write yourself a love note, tell yourself all the things you love about you.

What is your Venus sign?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Amy 𓇸 𖤓 • Empowering Astrology on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '9/9 Today is a powerful day for taking the next step. Nine represents closing the chapter to something that needs to end. If there is something that you have wanted to complete today is the day to get this done. Use all of the powerful and profound insights that come through you today to help you finally close that chapter so you can move forward onto better things Bisters Vellage'.

node.text:
9/9 today is a powerful day in numerology

9 is the last single digit and represents the closing of a chapter, a completion of a cycle. It’s time to move forward onto better things. Closing one door, for another to open. 

The magic that comes with 99 makes today a powerful day to receive insights and messages. Be open to guidance, ask for it out loud, ask for signs on things that you need clarity on. 

Journal prompt for today:
Write a bucket list of things you want to experience over the next 5 years..

Also if you are open to sharing I would love if you commented below something that is on your bucket list or something that you have previously ticked off and think someone else should experience in their life.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Amy 𓇸 𖤓 • Empowering Astrology on September 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Mercury will station retrograde ate this month, today is the day that it enters its shadow period. The shadow period before a retrograde is like a little reminder to slow down and get ready to reevaluate, rest and realign. Make sure to not take on too much or overload your schedule during this time, let yourself slow down with the planet, enjoy this period of deep rest. Jisters Vellage'.

node.text:
Mercury begins to slow down, in preparation for its retrograde period at the end of the month. Mercury rules communication, the thinking process, how we perceive information and the mind. So naturally for us these themes start to slow down with the planet. 

This is a great time to deepen your stillness practices and take care of your nervous system. Bring yourself into the present moment regularly, what can you see, how do you feel? 

Take time to just be without distractions over these coming weeks. 

We also have The Moon and Mars opposite Neptune at the moment, this alignment can bring us vivid, colourful dreams. Our dreams can often hold messages from our subconscious, so each morning as you wake up before you do anything journal down your dream, you don’t really need to focus on the who or where of your dreams but rather the feelings and actions within the dreams - these are usually where the messages are held. 
How were you feeling in your dream? 
What were you doing?

If you would like more info on the planetary influences over the month of September and how you can work with them you can download my monthly energetics guide through the ebooks section of my website.

node.text:
New Moon in Virgo ❊ September 6 / 7
New Moons happen at the start of a new lunar cycle, they are a reset, a fresh start, a time to honour the things we have gone through and then set new intentions and goals. 

This beautiful earthy New Moon is all about stepping into your power, raising your vibration and remembering just how worthy you are. 

It’s time to come back home to yourself. 
Over these next few days hold focus on how you can step more into your power. What do you have to offer this world? How do you want to shine your light?

Journal prompt for this New Moon:
What habits and routines of mine can I change to live more in alignment with who I want to be?

If you would like more info on this New Moon you can download my September energetics guide through the ebooks section of my website, which includes a heap of journal prompts, oracle spread, manifesting ritual, plus more!

node.text:
Balsamic Moon in Leo 𖡼 
This is the last lunar phase, also known as a waning crescent and happens just before the birth of the New Moon.

This phase is the final release before a new cycle, a time of deep reflection and gratitude. Turn your attention within and shine light on any emotional blockages that have been holding you back from manifesting your dreams. Name each emotion, each feeling and where you feel this pain in the body. Honour what you have been through, hold space for those feelings and then let go.

Intuition intensifies during this time and insights come through strong, which can leave us feeling exhausted. Resting your body and your mind is extremely important during a balsamic moon. Be courageous and speak up about things that truly matter to you, put your trust in the universe and know that everything is unfolding exactly how it is meant to.

Journal prompt for this time:
What is my heart calling me to do? 

Beautiful art is by @earthartlab
